<div class="rui:py-8">
  <%= heading text: "Theme", id: "theme", tag: "h2", class: "rui:font-bold rui:md:text-3xl rui:text-2xl rui:tracking-tight rui:mb-3" %>

  <div class="rui:prose rui:prose-neutral rui:dark:prose-invert rui:mb-6">
    <p>A theme is a set of <%= link_to "pre-built components", systems_path %> and <%= link_to "optional pages", root_path(anchor: "pages"), data: { action: "click->railsui-smooth#scroll"} %> that make it easy to get a massive head start on the design of your application.</p>
    <p>Your active theme: <span class="rui:bg-neutral-200/80 rui:text-neutral-800 rui:dark:bg-neutral-600/70 rui:dark:text-neutral-200 rui:font-medium rui:text-sm rui:rounded-sm rui:px-1 rui:py-0.5"><%= Railsui.config.theme.humanize %></span></p>
  </div>

  <ul class="rui:grid rui:md:grid-cols-3 rui:gap-6 rui:mb-16">
    <% Railsui::Default::THEMES.each do |key, theme| %>
      <li>
        <% theme_id = key.to_s %>

        <input type="radio" id="configuration_theme_<%= theme_id %>" value="<%= key %>" name="configuration[theme]" class="rui:sr-only rui:peer rui:group" <% if theme_id == Railsui.config.theme %>checked<% end %>>

        <label data-railsui-configuration-target="theme" for="configuration_theme_<%= theme_id %>" class="rui:bg-white rui:rounded-lg rui:overflow-clip rui:block rui:border rui:border-neutral-300 rui:focus:ring-4 rui:focus:ring-white rui:transition rui:duration-300 rui:dark:bg-neutral-700 rui:dark:border-neutral-600 rui:hover:shadow-xl rui:peer-checked:ring-4 rui:peer-checked:ring-black rui:relative rui:peer-checked:before:content-['Selected']
      rui:peer-checked:before:text-sm
      rui:peer-checked:before:absolute
      rui:peer-checked:before:top-0
      rui:peer-checked:before:left-0
      rui:peer-checked:before:bg-black/95
      rui:dark:peer-checked:before:bg-amber-300
      rui:dark:peer-checked:before:text-neutral-950
      rui:dark:peer-checked:ring-amber-300
      rui:peer-checked:before:backdrop-blur-sm
      rui:peer-checked:before:w-20 rui:peer-checked:before:px-1 rui:rui:peer-checked:before:py-0.5 rui:peer-checked:before:text-white rui:peer-checked:before:font-medium
      rui:peer-checked:before:rounded-br-lg
      rui:peer-checked:before:transition
      rui:peer-checked:before:animate-fade-in
      rui:peer-checked:before:text-center
      rui:peer-checked:shadow-xl
      rui:peer-checked:shadow-black/10">
          <%= image_tag theme[:thumbnail], alt: "#{theme[:name]} theme" %>
        </label>
        <div class="rui:mt-4 rui:flex rui:items-center rui:justify-between rui:gap-2">
          <p class="rui:font-semibold rui:text-base rui:my-2">
            <%= theme[:name] %>
          </p>
          <%= link_to theme[:preview_link], target: :_blank, class: "rui:inline-flex rui:text-sm rui:items-center rui:gap-2 rui:font-medium rui:text-sm rui:py-1 rui:px-2 rui:rounded-md rui:border rui:border-neutral-300 rui:dark:border-neutral-600 rui:hover:shadow-xs" do %>
            <span>Preview</span>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>

  <p class="rui:py-4 rui:tracking-wide rui:text-neutral-500 rui:dark:text-white">Theme FAQs</p>

  <dl class="rui:mt-2 rui:divide-y rui:divide-gray-200 rui:dark:divide-neutral-700 rui:mb-10">
    <details class="rui:group rui:py-4">
      <summary class="rui:flex rui:w-full rui:cursor-pointer rui:select-none rui:justify-between rui:text-left rui:text-base rui:font-semibold rui:leading-7 rui:text-neutral-900 rui:dark:text-neutral-200 rui:group-open:text-neutral-900 rui:dark:group-open:text-neutral-400 rui:[&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <div class="rui:flex rui:items-center rui:gap-2">
          Can I change my theme? <span class="rui:bg-yellow-300 rui:text-black rui:rounded-sm rui:px-1 rui:py-px rui:inline-flex rui:h-4 rui:items-center rui:uppercase rui:text-[9px]">New</span>
        </div>
        <svg class="rui:mt-0.5 rui:ml-4 rui:h-6 rui:w-6 rui:flex-none rui:stroke-neutral-300 rui:dark:stroke-neutral-400 rui:group-open:stroke-neutral-600" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 12H6"></path><path class="rui:group-open:hidden" d="M12 6v12"></path></svg>
      </summary>

      <div class="rui:prose rui:prose-neutral rui:dark:prose-invert rui:max-w-none rui:prose-a:font-semibold rui:prose-a:text-neutral-600 rui:dark:prose-a:text-neutral-400 rui:prose-a:hover:text-neutral-500 rui:prose-ol:list-decimal rui:py-6">
        <p>Yes, you can change your theme at any time. We strive to make this as easy as possible but it's not without some caveats.</p>

        <p>Here's what happens when you change your theme:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Rails UI generated pages (<code>app/views/rui</code>) and images (<code>app/assets/images/railsui</code>) are replaced with the newly chosen theme's files.
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Tip:</strong> To keep using any pages in the <code>app/views/rui</code> directory or images in the <code>app/assets/images/railsui</code> directory, copy these files to a backup location or elsewhere in your app before making changes. For best results, consider pages as code snippets for your app and treat them as read-only.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            Your custom colors will be preserved.
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Run <code>rails railsui:colors</code> to quickly see the default colors of your selected theme. If you want to see another theme's colors, run <code>rails 'railsui:colors[theme_name]'</code>.</p>
              </li>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Your <code>tailwind.config.js</code> file will be scanned and optimized to use the new theme's <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/railsui-tailwind-presets">Rails UI preset</a> along with other necessary Rails UI configuration settings.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="rui:group rui:py-4">
    <summary class="rui:flex rui:w-full rui:cursor-pointer rui:select-none rui:justify-between rui:text-left rui:text-base rui:font-semibold rui:leading-7 rui:text-neutral-900 rui:dark:text-neutral-200 rui:group-open:text-neutral-900 rui:dark:group-open:text-neutral-400 rui:[&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
      Do I need to use this form?

      <svg class="rui:mt-0.5 rui:ml-4 rui:h-6 rui:w-6 rui:flex-none rui:stroke-neutral-300 rui:dark:stroke-neutral-400 rui:group-open:stroke-neutral-600" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 12H6"></path><path class="group-open:hidden" d="M12 6v12"></path></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="rui:prose rui:prose-neutral rui:dark:prose-invert rui:max-w-none rui:prose-a:font-semibold rui:prose-a:text-neutral-600 rui:dark:prose-a:text-neutral-400 rui:prose-a:hover:text-neutral-500 rui:prose-ol:list-decimal rui:py-6">
      <p>No, you don't need to use this form. You can change your theme, colors, or pages at any time directly in the <code>config/railsui.yml</code> file. Use the Rails UI  generators (Run <code>rails g --help | grep 'railsui:'</code> to see the list of available railsui generators) to update your configuration via the command line.</p>

      <p>You can check <a href="https://railsui.com/docs" target="_blank">the documentation</a> to see a list of available default colors and pages bundled with each Rails UI theme.</p>

    </div>
  </details>
</dl>

<div class="rui:prose rui:prose-neutral rui:dark:prose-invert rui:max-w-none rui:prose-a:font-semibold rui:prose-a:text-neutral-600 rui:dark:prose-a:text-neutral-400 rui:prose-a:hover:text-neutral-500 rui:prose-ol:list-decimal rui:py-6">
  <p>Read more about <a href="https://railsui.com/docs/themes" target="_blank">themes</a> and <a href="https://railsui.com/docs/components" target="_blank">components</a> in the Rails UI documentation.</p>
</div>
</div>
